---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Ekklesia — Is This What Yahushua Had in Mind? — Nazaryah"
  description="The word 'church' doesn't appear in Hebrew Scripture. The called-out ones were called out to meet with Yahuah at His feasts. What happened to that? A series of snapshots from the modern church."
>
  <div class="ek-wrap">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="ek-hero">
      <p class="ek-eyebrow">nazaryah.com</p>
      <h1 class="ek-title">Is This the <span class="ek-red">Ekklesia</span>?</h1>
      <div class="ek-rule"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
    <section class="ek-intro">
      <p>
        <strong>The word "church" doesn't appear in Hebrew Scripture — because the concept doesn't exist there.</strong> The closest Hebrew equivalent is <em class="ek-red">miqra qodesh</em> (מקרא קדש) — a "set-apart calling out" — and every time it appears in Leviticus 23, it is attached to one of Yahuah's appointed times, the <em class="ek-red">Moedim</em>. The "called out ones" were called out <em>to meet with Him</em> at His feasts.
      </p>
      <p>
        When the Greek <em>ekklesia</em> replaced this Hebrew concept, it kept the phrase "called out" but severed the connection to the Moedim. Called out — but called out to <em>what</em>? The Hebrew answered that question. The Greek left it blank. And into that silence, men built buildings, created programs, and abandoned the very appointments the calling was about.
      </p>
      <p>
        Even the English word "church" doesn't come from <em>ekklesia</em>. It comes from the Germanic <em>kirche</em>, rooted in <em>kuriakos</em> — "belonging to a lord." The word itself was swapped. The early believers in Acts 2:46 met daily in homes and in the temple courts. No building fund. No programs. No 501(c)(3). Just a people set apart, keeping Torah, and meeting at the times Yahuah appointed.
      </p>
      <p>
        Today, thousands of church buildings stand where the Moedim once did. The feasts of Yahuah have been replaced by a man-made calendar. The "called out ones" gather on the wrong day, celebrate the wrong holidays, and have no idea what they were called out <em>for</em>.
      </p>
      <p class="ek-closing">
        What you see below is the result. These snapshots are not meant to mock — they are meant to make you ask one simple question: <strong>is this what Yahushua had in mind?</strong>
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── SNAPSHOTS ── -->
    <main class="ek-main">

      <!-- 1 -->
      <details class="ek-card">
        <summary class="ek-card-header">
          <span class="ek-num">01</span>
          <div class="ek-card-meta">
            <h2 class="ek-card-title">Drive-Thru Prayer</h2>
            <p class="ek-card-sub">Every Saturday 9–11am</p>
          </div>
          <span class="ek-arrow">&#9660;</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="ek-tags">
          <span class="ek-tag">Convenience Culture</span>
          <span class="ek-tag">Prayer</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ek-body">
          <div class="ek-placeholder">&#128247; Photo coming soon — have one? Send it in.</div>
          <p class="ek-observation">Prayer — the most intimate act between a soul and the Creator — reduced to a convenience window. Pull up, place your order, drive away. No relationship. No accountability. No community. Just a spiritual drive-thru on the way to brunch.</p>
          <blockquote class="ek-scripture">
            <p>"But when you pray, go into your inner room, shut your door, and pray to your Father who is in secret. And your Father, who sees in secret, will reward you."</p>
            <cite>— Matthew 6:6</cite>
          </blockquote>
          <p class="ek-contrast">Yahushua didn't say "roll down your window." He said shut your door. Prayer was never designed to be convenient — it was designed to be personal.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- 2 -->
      <details class="ek-card">
        <summary class="ek-card-header">
          <span class="ek-num">02</span>
          <div class="ek-card-meta">
            <h2 class="ek-card-title">The Building Fund</h2>
            <p class="ek-card-sub">Give toward our new $12M facility</p>
          </div>
          <span class="ek-arrow">&#9660;</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="ek-tags">
          <span class="ek-tag">Money</span>
          <span class="ek-tag">Buildings</span>
          <span class="ek-tag">Priorities</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ek-body">
          <div class="ek-placeholder">&#128247; Photo coming soon — have one? Send it in.</div>
          <p class="ek-observation">Millions poured into buildings with coffee bars, gymnasiums, and state-of-the-art lighting — while the poor in the congregation struggle to pay rent. The early ekklesia met in homes. Yahushua said the temple would be torn down. Yet the modern church keeps building them bigger.</p>
          <blockquote class="ek-scripture">
            <p>"Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up."</p>
            <cite>— John 2:19</cite>
          </blockquote>
          <p class="ek-contrast">Yahushua was talking about His body, not a building campaign. The temple of Yahuah was never meant to be a brick-and-mortar empire. You are the temple.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- 3 -->
      <details class="ek-card">
        <summary class="ek-card-header">
          <span class="ek-num">03</span>
          <div class="ek-card-meta">
            <h2 class="ek-card-title">The Church Committee</h2>
            <p class="ek-card-sub">Board of Directors, Deacon Board, Finance Committee, Worship Committee…</p>
          </div>
          <span class="ek-arrow">&#9660;</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="ek-tags">
          <span class="ek-tag">Corporate Structure</span>
          <span class="ek-tag">Leadership</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ek-body">
          <div class="ek-placeholder">&#128247; Photo coming soon — have one? Send it in.</div>
          <p class="ek-observation">When did the assembly of the set-apart ones become a Fortune 500 company? Committees, boards, org charts, HR departments, branding teams. Where in Scripture did the apostles form a marketing committee?</p>
          <blockquote class="ek-scripture">
            <p>"Not so with you. Instead, whoever wants to become great among you must be your servant."</p>
            <cite>— Matthew 20:26</cite>
          </blockquote>
          <p class="ek-contrast">Yahushua's model was servanthood, not corporate governance. The early assembly had elders and deacons — not CEOs and board members.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- 4 -->
      <details class="ek-card">
        <summary class="ek-card-header">
          <span class="ek-num">04</span>
          <div class="ek-card-meta">
            <h2 class="ek-card-title">501(c)(3) Status</h2>
            <p class="ek-card-sub">A church incorporated under the state</p>
          </div>
          <span class="ek-arrow">&#9660;</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="ek-tags">
          <span class="ek-tag">Government</span>
          <span class="ek-tag">Tax Exemption</span>
          <span class="ek-tag">Authority</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ek-body">
          <div class="ek-placeholder">&#128247; Photo coming soon — have one? Send it in.</div>
          <p class="ek-observation">To gain tax-exempt status, churches register as corporations — beholden to the government for what they can say, do, and teach. They traded the headship of the Messiah for the headship of the state. And most don't even realize the exchange they made.</p>
          <blockquote class="ek-scripture">
            <p>"No one can serve two masters. Either you will hate the one and love the other, or you will be devoted to the one and despise the other."</p>
            <cite>— Matthew 6:24</cite>
          </blockquote>
          <p class="ek-contrast">The assembly's only head is Yahushua. When the government can revoke your "status" for speaking truth, who is really in charge?</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- 5 -->
      <details class="ek-card">
        <summary class="ek-card-header">
          <span class="ek-num">05</span>
          <div class="ek-card-meta">
            <h2 class="ek-card-title">The Merch Table</h2>
            <p class="ek-card-sub">T-shirts, coffee mugs, bumper stickers, and branded journals</p>
          </div>
          <span class="ek-arrow">&#9660;</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="ek-tags">
          <span class="ek-tag">Commerce</span>
          <span class="ek-tag">Merchandise</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ek-body">
          <div class="ek-placeholder">&#128247; Photo coming soon — have one? Send it in.</div>
          <p class="ek-observation">Tables set up in the lobby selling branded merchandise. Sound familiar? Yahushua had something to say about commerce in the place of worship — and He didn't say it quietly.</p>
          <blockquote class="ek-scripture">
            <p>"Take these things away! Do not make My Father's house a house of merchandise!"</p>
            <cite>— John 2:16</cite>
          </blockquote>
          <p class="ek-contrast">He flipped the tables then. What would He do now?</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="ek-cta">
        <p class="ek-cta-pre">This is not about embarrassing anyone. It's about asking a simple question:</p>
        <p class="ek-cta-quote">"Is this what Yahushua had in mind?"</p>
        <p class="ek-cta-sub">Have a snapshot to share? Send it to <a href="/contact" class="ek-link">nazaryah.com/contact</a></p>
      </div>

    </main>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ek-wrap {
    background: #0D0B0A;
    color: #D4C5B0;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  /* ── HERO ── */
  .ek-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
  }

  .ek-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 6px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #5a4e42;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .ek-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #E8DED0;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .ek-red { color: #C4463A; }

  .ek-rule {
    width: 40px;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(196,70,58,0.5), transparent);
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
  }

  /* ── INTRO ── */
  .ek-intro {
    max-width: 740px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
  }

  .ek-intro p {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.1rem);
    color: #C5B8A5;
    line-height: 1.85;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .ek-intro p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .ek-intro strong { color: #E8DED0; font-weight: 500; }
  .ek-intro em { font-style: italic; }

  .ek-closing {
    color: #A89B8C !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── MAIN ── */
  .ek-main {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 5rem;
  }

  /* ── CARDS ── */
  .ek-card {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: border-color 0.3s;
  }

  .ek-card[open] {
    border-color: rgba(196,70,58,0.3);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
  }

  .ek-card-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .ek-card-header::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .ek-card-header:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.015); }

  .ek-num {
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid rgba(196,70,58,0.4);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #C4463A;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    line-height: 36px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .ek-card-meta { flex: 1; }

  .ek-card-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 3vw, 1.4rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #E8DED0;
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', Georgia, serif;
  }

  .ek-card-sub {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: #5a4e42;
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .ek-arrow {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: #5a4e42;
    transition: transform 0.3s;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .ek-card[open] .ek-arrow {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  /* ── TAGS ── */
  .ek-tags {
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .ek-tag {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.625rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    background: rgba(196,70,58,0.12);
    color: #E8DED0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(196,70,58,0.22);
  }

  /* ── BODY ── */
  .ek-body {
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    animation: ek-fadein 0.35s ease;
  }

  @keyframes ek-fadein {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-6px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  .ek-placeholder {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding: 2rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(196,70,58,0.05);
    border: 1px dashed rgba(196,70,58,0.2);
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #5a4e42;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .ek-observation {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #C5B8A5;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .ek-scripture {
    border-left: 3px solid #C4463A;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(196,70,58,0.04);
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }

  .ek-scripture p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #E8DED0;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .ek-scripture cite {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: #C4463A;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .ek-contrast {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #A89B8C;
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── CTA ── */
  .ek-cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .ek-cta-pre {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #5a4e42;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: 0 auto 0.75rem;
  }

  .ek-cta-quote {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 1.75rem);
    color: #E8DED0;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .ek-cta-sub {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #5a4e42;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ek-link {
    color: #C4463A;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .ek-link:hover { color: #d45a50; }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .ek-card-header { padding: 1rem; }
    .ek-tags { padding: 0 1rem 0.75rem; }
    .ek-body { padding: 0 1rem 1.5rem; }
  }
</style>
